Some facts..<br>
<br>
<br>
&quot;Almost all of his posts are negative and sometimes delusional.&quot;<br>
<br>
I have strong opinions that just don't happen to agree with the norm in regards to EQ and many classes in EQ.  I am not afraid to post them.<br>
<br>
 &quot;On the Saryrn Tavern, he used to constantly post that certain people on the Saryrn Server had it in for him due to some past incident that occurred while he was a guild leader or something to that effect.&quot;<br>
<br>
Many people did &quot;have it our for me&quot; for consistantly poining out that mages were more then mod rods (mod rod 1 at the time) and more then CoH.  They also did not like the fact that I stood up to the gang at the Tavern and pointed out how the way they ran the server was basiclly morally wrong.<br>
<br>
Paranoid?  I think not, I spent the better part of 2 years on that server getting trained and KSed.. and in general blacklisted for opinions stated on a message board.<br>
<br>
Eventually I gave up and moved to SH which has proven to be MUCH better.  <br>
<br>
<br>
&quot;I have seen more than a few loons on various EQ messageboards, and I must count Rthen as one of them. He is a strange, deluded person who constantly posts negative and paranoid thoughts on the various messageboards.&quot;<br>
<br>
I post critical things in regards to the mage class and nothing more.  Mages on SH are treated well it is not a &quot;Saryrn&quot;.<br>
<br>
I post critical things in regards to the mage class because it is currently the only issue I have with the game.  It is the only class I wish to play and I would like it fixed.  <br>
<br>
I'm not afraid to stand up to opression in game or out of game.<br>
I think it is silly what Saryrn's celebrities put me though for my stance on Mages and my opinions on Server leadership.  Quite amusing... <br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
&quot;Personally, I hope you don't ban him. It will only feed his paranoid delusions and cause him to spew forth more negative rubbish. <br>
Natharius Bladestorm<br>
Lvl 55 Mage<br>
Saryrn<br>
Isengard&quot;<br>
<br>
Did you know that one of the founders of your guild made it his personal lifes work in EQ to insure my gaming experience was ruined (until he quit the game) because they felt I needed to pay 20k to cover somehting a former guild member of mine did?<br>
<br>
I found out later it was a setup to extort plat from people.  The guild member in question was rotated though various small guilds and then would do &quot;somehting&quot; to warrent extortion.<br>
<br>
I never paid the 20k and despite Isengauards efforts I am still playing the game.<br>
<br>
